Catherine MCDONALD, Appellee, v. Carroll G. DYKES and Victor-Lynn Lines, Inc., Defendants and Third-Party Plaintiffs, Appellants (William J. O’Brien, Third-Party Defendant, Appellee). No. 9390. Circuit Court of Appeals, Third Circuit. Argued Oct. 7, 1947. Decided Oct. 9, 1947. Raymond A. White, Jr., of Philadelphia, Pa., for appellants. Harold S. Baile, of Philadelphia, Pa. (Pepper, Bodine & Stokes, of Philadelphia, Pa., on the brief), for appellee O’Brien. William P. Desmond, of Chester, Pa., for appellee McDonald.

Before BIGGS, ALBERT LEE STEPHENS, and MARIS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment of the court below will be affirmed on the opinion of Judge McGran-ery, 6 F.R.D. 569.
